title: Injured Evergreen football player dies at Harborview
text:
Injured Evergreen football player dies at Harborview Originally published October 5, 2015 at 1:26 pm A high school senior who suffered a critical injury late in a Friday night football game has died, an official at Harborview Medical Center said Monday. By JoNel Aleccia Seattle Times staff reporter 
A high school senior who suffered a critical injury late in a Friday night football game has died, an official at Harborview Medical Center said Monday. 
Evergreen player Kenny Bui succumbed shortly before noon Monday to unspecified injuries, said Susan Gregg, a hospital spokeswoman. Family members were adamant about requesting privacy. 
“He has a lot of friends who will support the family through this really hard time,” Gregg said. 
Bui was among two high school students seriously injured in games over the weekend. Adna senior David Young suffered a neck fracture and remains in satisfactory condition at Harborview, his stepfather said. Most Read Stories
